   Club, Leuven, BELGIUM, OCT 30-NOV 01, 2014},
Abstract = {In this paper, we presented a probabilistic framework to predict Bus
   Bunching (BB) occurrences in real-time. It uses both historical and
   real-time data to approximate the headway distributions on the further
   stops of a given route by employing both offline and online supervised
   learning techniques. Such approximations are incrementally calculated by
   reusing the latest prediction residuals to update the further ones.
   These update rules extend the Perceptron's delta rule by assuming an
   adaptive beta value based on the current context. These distributions
   are then used to compute the likelihood of forming a bus platoon on a
   further stop - which may trigger an threshold-based BB alarm. This
   framework was evaluated using real-world data about the trips of 3 bus
   lines throughout an year running on the city of Porto, Portugal. The
   results are promising.},
