   we explore the use of generative AI tools within this domain. More
   specifically, we focus on a topic related to sustainable passenger
   transportation, that is, the handling of disturbances in public
   transport when it comes to bus bunching and bus bridging. The first of
   these concepts is related to analyzing situations where we observe two
   or more buses of the same line following close to each other without
   being planned deliberately and the second is related to the case where
   buses are used to replace broken connections in other systems, such as
