Abstract = {Buses have an inherent tendency to bunch due to randomness in passenger
   demand and congestion. Many sophisticated control strategies have been
   developed to reduce bus bunching, however, few of them have been
   implemented in high frequency real services. Building upon a control
   strategy comprised of a rolling horizon mathematical programming model
   that yields the optimal holding time that minimizes user-waiting
   times(6), we have developed real-time software and implemented it on two
   bus services in Santiago using different technologies to communicate the
   instructions to bus drivers. The results presented in this paper are
   encouraging, on the days the system was implemented less bus bunching
   was observed, which translated in fewer headway-irregularity fines.
   Moreover lower passenger fare evasion was observed when the bus control
   strategy was used. (C) 2014 Published by Elsevier B.V.},
