Month = {SEP 1},
Abstract = {Bus bunching deteriorates transit service quality and passengers'
   experience. The modeling and prediction of bus operation states are
   essential for improving the quality of transit service. Due to the
   nature of traffic evolution and state transition, bunching-oriented
   modeling based on bus operation state is more intuitive when compared
   with the headway-based modeling approach. This work explicitly predicted
   bus operation state by modeling the dynamic evolution of different
   states. Five different bus operation states were defined and classified
   by the K-means algorithm, and the dynamic state evolution was formulated
   as a Markov chain model. Finally, a multinomial logistic model was
   developed to predict the bus operation state. A case study was designed
   to test the performance of the proposed model based on the Global
   Positioning System (GPS) trajectory data collected from four bus routes
   in Xi'an, China. The results showed that the proposed model was able to
   accurately predict the bus operation states.},
