   technologies. In this study, we developed an optimization model to
   quantify how the CAV benefits the route-level transit operations if all
   current non-automated buses are converted into autonomous buses. A
   bi-objective mixed integer programming model is established to minimize
   passenger waiting times and maximize passenger flows considering all
   buses are running on a bus dedicated lane. By taking one actual bus
   route in Beijing as a case study, we computed the operational
   performance indicators of non-automated bus based on smart card and GPS
   data, and compared with the optimized bus routes with CAV technologies.
